TY  - JOUR
TI  - Notching R&D Investment with Corporate Income Tax Cuts in China
AU  - Chen, Zhao
AU  - Liu, Zhikuo
AU  - Serrato, Juan Carlos Suárez
AU  - Xu, Daniel Yi
AB  - [We study a Chinese policy that awards substantial tax cuts to firms with R&D investment over a threshold or “notch.” Quasi-experimental variation and administrative tax data show a significant increase in reported R&D that is partly driven by firms relabeling expenses as R&D. Structural estimates show relabeling accounts for 24.2 percent of reported R&D and that doubling R&D would increase productivity by 9 percent. Policy simulations show that firm selection and relabeling determine the cost-effectiveness of stimulating R&D, that notch-based policies are more effective than tax credits when relabeling is prevalent, and that modest spillovers justify the program from a welfare perspective.]
